  <div class="container">
    <h1>Ad Testing</h1>
    <p>This document was last updated on <!--rinline format(Sys.time(), "%A %d %B %Y") --></p>
    <p>Below is a simple game in which your objective is to get the best overall click through rate.</p>
    <p>The game is kind of "turn based" with each turn lasting a week.</p>
    <p>When setting up for your turn you can add new adverts and pause or reactivate old adverts. You can also choose "rotate evenly" or "optimise for..." ad serving settings. The meaning of these corresponds to the AdWords equivalent.</p>
    <p>You may also want to change the number of weekly impressions for the ad group. This setting is adjustable because a good strategy for a low traffic ad group might not be the same as a good strategy for a high traffic ad group.</p>
    <p>Click "New Advert" to get started and then when you are ready for the first week click "Run".</p>
    <hr/>
    <div id="testgame">
    </div>
  </div>
  <script type="text/javascript">
    var elmDiv = document.getElementById('testgame');
    var elmapp = Elm.embed(Elm.Tester, elmDiv,{startTime: Date.now()})
  </script>
